          "Obtaining Certification",
          "Certificate Obtained (1) vs Certificate Not Obtained (0)",
          "338223 registrations ",
          "HarvardX courses",
          "Student Characteristics, \nLMS logs,\nPerformance on the Platform",
          "[course_id, userid_DI, registered, viewed, explored, final_cc_cname_, LoE_DI, YoB, genderr, grade, start_time_DI, last_event_DI, nchapters, ndays_act, nforum_posts, nnplay_video, nevents, roles, incomplete_flag]",
          "End of Program",
          "Authors use co-training to perform semi-supervised learning - training 2 different classifiers on data (represented by 2 redudant, but independent views) and obtainning predictions on unlabeled data. The highest confidence predictions are subsequently joined to a new view and removed from the unlabeled set.\n\n The creation of the views (and the independence of the features selected from each view) is done using semi-decoupled co-training - highly correlated variables are placed on the same view. Low correlated features are placed into 2 views (important features are also separated): \n\nThe selection was donne using DT Feature Importances and Correlation Coefficients.\n",
          "Logistic Regression, \nRandom Forest, \nLightGBM, \nGBoost,\nSelf-Training, \nCo-Training, \nTri-Training\nSemi-Decoupling Features for Self-Supervised Learning",
          "k-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "k=2\n{F1-Score: 0.9946 - Author’s model, Precision: 0.9908 -  Author’s model, Recall: 0.9983}\n\nk=3\n{F1-Score: 0.9941 - Author’s model (2:1), Precision: 0.9898 -  Author’s model (1:2), Recall: 0.9990 (2:1)}\n\nk=5\n{F1-Score: 0.9953 - Author’s model (2:8), Precision: 0.9920 -  Author’s model (8:2), Recall: 0.9986 (8:2)}\n",
          "Authors use a public dataset to validate their Semi-Supervised Learning algorithm - HarvardX is one, but there is also data from other contexts. \n\nMultiple values of k for CV were tested: 2, 3 and 5. The proportions for training and testing are tested (e.g. for k=3, 2 folds train/1  val and 1 fold train/2 folds val are tested). \n\nResults seem extremely impressive. \n\n",
          "Data dependent: Co-Training requires a substantial number of features that allow the creation of the dual views. \n\nCumulative addition of noise with the increase initerations. \n\nRisk of underfitting if features are still semi-decoupled. \n\nRisk of computational overload if number of features is too large.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
